item.description:
Its pretty common that you want to remove a file that has already been commited to a remote repository. There are couple of options
rm &lt;file-name&gt; git add &lt;file-name&gt;
OR do `git rm &lt;file-name&gt;
Essentially git rm is combination of first 2 commands.
git rm --cached will remove the file from the index (staging it for deletion on the next commit), but keep your copy in the local file system
